  "doc_id": "38993",
  "text": "1) Interpolation: Early work on video frame interpolation has focused on establishing block-wise [CITATION_1] and/or pixel-wise [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] correspondences between available frames. Improved performance has been achieved via coarse-to-fine estimation [CITATION_4] , texture decomposition [CITATION_5] , and deep neural networks (DNN) [CITATION_6] . Recent DNN-based approaches include deep voxel flow [CITATION_7] , separable convolution [CITATION_8] , flow computation and interpolation CNN [CITATION_9] . 2) Prediction: Recent work on future frame prediction has proposed to use adversarial nets [CITATION_10] , temporal consistency losses [CITATION_11] and layered cross convolution networks [CITATION_12] . 3) Motion deblur: Recent work on resolving a sharp video/image from blurry image(s) has leveraged adversarial loss [CITATION_13] , gated fusion network [CITATION_14] , ordering-invariant loss [CITATION_15] , etc.",
